g.title: filter_KUBEIPVSFILTER
g.text: -m conntrack --ctstate NEW -m set --match-set KUBE-IPVS-IPS dst -j REJECT --reject-with icmp-port-unreachable

g.title: filter_KUBENODEPORT
g.text: -m comment --comment "Kubernetes health check node port" -m set --match-set KUBE-HEALTH-CHECK-NODE-PORT dst -j ACCEPT

g.title: filter_KUBEFIREWALL
g.text: ! -s 127.0.0.0/8 -d 127.0.0.0/8 -m comment --comment "block incoming localnet connections" -m conntrack ! --ctstate RELATED,ESTABLISHED,DNAT -j DROP

g.title: filter_KUBEFORWARD
g.text: -m comment --comment "kubernetes forwarding conntrack rule" -m conntrack --ctstate RELATED,ESTABLISHED -j ACCEPT

g.title: nat_KUBESERVICES
g.text: -m comment --comment "Kubernetes service lb portal" -m set --match-set KUBE-LOAD-BALANCER dst,dst -j KUBE-LOAD-BALANCER
! -s 10.244.0.0/16 -m comment --comment "Kubernetes service cluster ip + port for masquerade purpose" -m set --match-set KUBE-CLUSTER-IP dst,dst -j KUBE-MARK-MASQ

g.title: nat_KUBEPOSTROUTING
g.text: -m comment --comment "Kubernetes endpoints dst ip:port, source ip for solving hairpin purpose" -m set --match-set KUBE-LOOP-BACK dst,dst,src -j MASQUERADE
-m comment --comment "kubernetes service traffic requiring SNAT" -j MASQUERADE --random-fully

g.title: nat_KUBEMARKMASQ
g.text: Kubernetes nodeport TCP port for masquerade purpose
Kubernetes service cluster ip + port for masquerade purpose

g.title: nat_KUBENODEPORT
g.text: -p tcp -m comment --comment "Kubernetes nodeport TCP port for masquerade purpose" -m set --match-set KUBE-NODE-PORT-TCP dst -j KUBE-MARK-MASQ
